pipeline_summary.name: Airflow Database Cleanup
pipeline_summary.description: Maintenance workflow that periodically cleans old metadata entries from Airflow's MetaStore database tables to prevent excessive data accumulation.

components.name: Extract Cleanup Configuration
components.description: Loads and validates cleanup configuration parameters from DAG run configuration and Airflow Variables, calculates the maximum retention date, and pushes it to XCom for downstream use.

upstream_policy.description: No upstream dependencies; this is the first task in the linear pipeline.

connections.purpose: Access Airflow MetaStore via default SQLAlchemy session

components.name: Cleanup Airflow MetaDB
components.description: Deletes old entries from Airflow metadata tables based on the calculated max_date and configurable retention rules.
outputs: Deletion logs / summary of cleaned rows (XCom)

upstream_policy.description: Executes after successful completion of extract_cleanup_configuration.

connections.purpose: Access Airflow MetaStore via default SQLAlchemy session

description.default: Maintenance workflow that periodically cleans old metadata entries from Airflow's MetaStore database tables to prevent excessive data accumulation.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

max_db_entry_age_in_days.description: Maximum age of database entries (in days) to retain before cleanup. Pulled from Airflow Variable 'airflow_db_cleanup__max_db_entry_age_in_days'.

provide_context.description: Flag indicating that Airflow context should be provided to the Python callable.

DATABASE_OBJECTS.description: List of Airflow metadata tables and their retention rules to be cleaned.

ENABLE_DELETE.description: When true, actual deletions are performed; when false, the task runs in dryrun mode.

ALERT_EMAIL_ADDRESSES.description: Commaseparated list of email addresses to receive alerts on task failures.

consumes: Airflow MetaStore tables (DagRun, TaskInstance, Log, XCom, SlaMiss, DagModel, TaskReschedule, TaskFail, RenderedTaskInstanceFields, ImportError, Job/BaseJob, etc.)

sources: Airflow DAG run configuration parameters (provided at trigger time)
Airflow Variable 'airflow_db_cleanup__max_db_entry_age_in_days' stored in the MetaStore DB
sinks: Deleted rows from Airflow MetaStore tables (DagRun, TaskInstance, Log, XCom, SlaMiss, DagModel, TaskReschedule, TaskFail, RenderedTaskInstanceFields, ImportError, Job/BaseJob, etc.)
Alert email sent via SMTP on task failure
intermediate_datasets: XCom payload 'max_date' passed from extract_cleanup_configuration to cleanup_airflow_metadb
